      "content": "that sounds like the background is basically being used as a proxy for character. so you're saying if someone comes from a \"stable\" area they're assumed to be more responsible, but if they're from an \"underserved\" area, the law assumes they're more dangerous or less capable of reform? even though they both committed the exact same crime?",
