      "content": "That is precisely the underlying bias that the legal system often struggles with, where socioeconomic status becomes a proxy for inherent character. The perception is that stability equates to good moral fiber, while instability is interpreted as a failure of character, even when the crime itself is identical. This disparity is a direct reflection of systemic prejudice in how judges and juries perceive different social classes.",
